  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "This package provides a server-side implementation of the FIDO Device Onboard (FDO) specification, written in Go. FDO is an open standard for the late binding of device credentials, allowing for automated and secure on-boarding of devices when they are first powered on in their final location.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* github.com/jackc/pgx/v5: github.com/jackc/pgx: Memory-safety vulnerability (CVE-2026-33816)\n\n* crypto/tls: golang: Go crypto/tls: Denial of Service via multiple TLS 1.3 key update messages (CVE-2026-32283)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
